BBNaija alumni, Rico Swarvey has advised single ladies to reduce the number of tattoos inked on their bodies. The reality TV star and singer took to his Twitter handle to give the advice. “Ladies, stop decorating your bodies with tattoos,” he tweeted.   Yvonne Nelson weighs in on why people get married     Regina Daniels gets two new tattoos     Davido, Adekunle Gold headline Pharrel William’s Something…   Continuing, the law graduate of Babcock University said: “A little bit is cool but when it is too much, it scares the hell out of responsible men.” Rico Swarvey grabbed fame after appearing on Big Brother Naija Season 3, also known as Big Brother Naija: Double Wahala. He was evicted from the show a few weeks before the finale and has since been pursuing a career in acting and singing.